  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 10</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 3</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 26 | <b>Successes:</b> 6</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 14 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 30</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, E, Mob</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>One of Maito Gai's signature techniques, you punch or kick with extreme speed, causing friction that creates small fireballs to assault your enemies. Make an (ranged) unarmed touch attack at the target, using your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier for the attack roll. On hit, the attack deals 1d6+1 fire damage. You suffer a -4 penalty to Learn checks when learning this technique if you do not have the Gouken feat.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Empower:</b> Spend 2 Chakra to throw an additional fireball, up to 1 per level or 15 total, whichever is lower. Each fireball can target a creature in range (the same creature can be targeted multiple times), and requires an attack roll (as above).</p>\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
